result.execSummary:
The defendant Alejandro Ruiz was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Alejandro Ruiz is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Alejandro Ruiz was found guilty of OWI (5th), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Alejandro Ruiz in court with attorney John j Forrestal.  Ronald Dague appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Pursuant to plea negotiations, and on motion of the State, Court ordered COUNT 2 DISMISSED.  Defendant changes plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Court found that defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights. Plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  Court advised the defendant that as a convicted felon he may no longer use or possess any firearms; also he may not vote in any election until his civil rights have been restored.  Court further advised that if he is not a US citizen, deportation is possible. 

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, Defense and Defendant.  The Court sentenced defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT in the Wisconsin State Prisons for 4 YEARS 6 MONTHS.  INITIAL CONFINEMENT of 2 YEARS 6 MONTHS and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 2 YEARS, consecutive to 14CF2929.  Court STAYED sentence and placed the defendant on PROBATION for a period of 3 YEARS 6 MONTHS with the following conditions for probation and extended supervision:
Defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and is not eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  
-Defendant to pay a fine in the amount of $1,200.00 PLUS Court costs and all applicable surcharges and assessments.  Bail on deposit to be applied.  Remaining balance to be returned to person who posted. 
-Defendant is to provide a DNA sample and pay the related surcharge out of cash bail on deposit. 
-No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause
-Cooperate with agent
-Cooperate with any correctional programs recommended
-Follow all rules of probation and extended supervision
-Pay all supervision fees 
-Obtain/maintain full-time employment 
-AODA assessment and any recommended treatment
-Absolute sobriety with random urine screens and breathalyzers
-No alcohol or controlled substances
-Defendant to perform 50 hours of community service
-Court suspends defendant's driving privileges for 2 years
-Court ordered ignition interlock for 2 years
-As a condition of probation, Court ordered defendant serve 1 YEAR in the House of Corrections.  First 90 days is straight time, remaining sentence with Huber release privileges for work/treatment.  No good time credit.  Defendant taken into custody. 

Filed, Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence
Filed, Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief
Filed, Ineligible Voting Notice and Acknowledgement
